==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Afterthought
<hw>Aft"er*thought`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Reflection after an act; later or subsequent thought.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an action taken after another action and related to
the first action, which would normally or optimally be done along with
the first action; -- <as>as, to do something as an
<ex>afterthought</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a feature or part added to a device, not thought of
in its original design.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Afterward</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Afterwards</ent>⟦br⟧
